1
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:43,350
Yes.

2
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:45,980
Okay, got it.

3
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:47,210
What did he say?

4
00:00:49,310 --> 00:00:51,120
That Dr. Kang Shi Young...

5
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,930
is still unconscious.

6
00:00:57,270 --> 00:00:59,080
Chief, what should we do?

7
00:01:03,090 --> 00:01:04,380
Get me a hazmat suit.

8
00:01:08,310 --> 00:01:10,400
Give me a hazmat suit. I'm going in.

9
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,560
Going in where?

10
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:14,180
No one is allowed in the
center right now.

11
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:16,650
The suspected patient
was admitted for

12
00:01:16,650 --> 00:01:19,050
headaches starting over a year ago.

13
00:01:19,050 --> 00:01:20,800
If the symptoms are recent,

14
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,520
it might not be the Nipah virus.

15
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,850
Regardless, no one's
allowed in right now.

16
00:01:24,850 --> 00:01:26,700
Until he's diagnosed as not.

17
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:29,500
And there are doctors inside.

18
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,120
Why must you go in, Dr. Cha?

19
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,290
The suspected patient is
showing new symptoms,

20
00:01:33,290 --> 00:01:34,380
and it's getting worse.

21
00:01:34,380 --> 00:01:36,490
Plus, one of the residents
is unconscious.

22
00:01:39,570 --> 00:01:41,640
- Give me a hazmat suit.
- No.

23
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:45,230
Director has stressed
we follow protocol.

24
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:47,570
You can't solve anything
by going in there.

25
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:50,460
No one may enter for
whatever reasons.

26
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:51,400
Never!

27
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:54,890
Chief.

28
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:03,890
We'll follow the protocol.

29
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:06,750
Dr. Kwon is right.

30
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:09,290
You can't solve anything by going in.

31
00:02:09,290 --> 00:02:11,320
Call Dr. Lee Yoo Joon.

32
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,440
Now.

33
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,210
My baby!

34
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,140
What happened?

35
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:25,750
What's going on here?

36
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,040
My child is inside...

37
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,750
We suspected a Nipah virus patient.

38
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,070
What about my child?

39
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:33,300
- Is she okay?
- We'll find out.

40
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:36,250
My child has juvenile diabetes.

41
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,210
She didn't even have lunch...

42
00:02:39,210 --> 00:02:40,810
If she doesn't eat something soon,

43
00:02:40,810 --> 00:02:43,390
she'll go into hypoglycemic shock!

44
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:45,030
I have to go in.

45
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:46,470
Please open it.

46
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:47,960
Right now!

47
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,800
Seo Jin!

48
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,140
Seo Jin!

49
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:53,690
I think we have a situation to resolve.

50
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:56,490
Glucagon...
[ Glucagon: a peptide hormone ]

51
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:58,650
and a hazmat suit. Give them to me.

52
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,150
Someone has to go in.

53
00:03:04,210 --> 00:03:05,340
It's a must.

54
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:12,350
Passing through, please move aside.

55
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,750
Are we going out now?

56
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:22,010
Can we leave now?

57
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:23,900
- Can we leave?
- Step back.

58
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:26,010
No one is allowed out.

59
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:27,810
If we can't go out...

60
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,370
why open the door?

61
00:03:29,370 --> 00:03:31,340
No one is going out...

62
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:33,410
but someone is coming in.

63
00:03:36,410 --> 00:03:37,470
Dr. Kang.

64
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:40,790
Dr. Kang!

65
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:43,500
Dr. Kang!

66
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,260
Dr. Kang.

67
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:48,780
Dr. Kang!

68
00:04:12,930 --> 00:04:14,450
How is the patient?

69
00:04:14,450 --> 00:04:16,570
His seizures stopped.

70
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,890
- Check his condition.
- Okay.

71
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,620
Kang Shi Young.

72
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:26,240
Are you awake?

73
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,770
Dr. Cha...

74
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:38,890
[ Doctor John ]
[ Episode 8: To understand someone ]

75
00:04:42,030 --> 00:04:43,500
It's all right.

76
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,940
You did well.

77
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:59,000
- I'll be back in 10 minutes.
- Okay.

78
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,240
You'll be fine, okay?

79
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:04,510
How is it over there?

80
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,840
I don't know yet.

81
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,570
But Sunbae, why did you come in?

82
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:14,170
You're going in?

83
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:16,570
I have a reason for going in.

84
00:05:16,570 --> 00:05:20,290
If I don't, I think I'll regret it forever.

85
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,860
I'm sorry.

86
00:05:35,030 --> 00:05:37,110
I'm truly sorry.

87
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:44,250
Dr. Cha, why did you come in here?

88
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:46,220
Why are you here?

89
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,380
How is your vision?

90
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:54,790
Can you see well?

91
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:56,590
I said, why are you here?

92
00:05:58,060 --> 00:05:59,750
I see some swelling.

93
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:01,340
Are you dizzy or nauseous?

94
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:03,890
What about your senses?

95
00:06:03,890 --> 00:06:05,400
Do you feel this?

96
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,290
- Dr. Cha...
- Answer me.

97
00:06:12,410 --> 00:06:14,040
I'm okay.

98
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:17,390
Good. Then get up slowly.

99
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:29,010
But why did you come in here?

100
00:06:29,010 --> 00:06:30,800
I'm not here for you.

101
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:00,560
Get up.

102
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,450
Are you okay?

103
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:08,810
Yes, I'm fine.

104
00:07:08,810 --> 00:07:10,210
How is the patient?

105
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:11,270
He fainted earlier.

106
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,840
His pulse sped up,
but it's stable again.

107
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:16,920
Palpitations.
[ Palpitations: Hard, fast and/or
irregular heartbeats ]

108
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:20,100
[ Palpitations: Hard, fast and/or
irregular heartbeats ]

109
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,580
The symptoms are
throughout his body.

110
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:34,180
His respiratory and circulatory
system nerves are dying.

111
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:36,880
What we must do now is

112
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:40,100
to diagnose him before
his condition worsens.

113
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,860
Of course, we assume
it's not the Nipah virus.

114
00:08:06,770 --> 00:08:10,290
[ Symptoms - Cough, Fever... ]

115
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:13,300
[ Cough, Fever... ]

116
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,580
You'll really do this?

117
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:25,820
It's a highly contagious
and lethal virus.

118
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:29,230
Also, you're part of the
high-risk group, Dr. Cha.

119
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:35,540
Think of this...

120
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:38,000
as a hostage situation.

121
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,610
A disease inside the
patient is the culprit.

122
00:08:40,610 --> 00:08:43,170
All of us locked up in
here are hostages.

123
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:45,460
And I'm the negotiator.

124
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:46,970
Is this fun for you?

125
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:48,350
Does it look fun?

126
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,940
As you said, I should be

127
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:54,690
out of here faster than
anyone and I really want to.

128
00:08:54,690 --> 00:08:55,810
So help me.

129
00:08:55,810 --> 00:08:57,590
Catch the culprit as fast as we can.

130
00:08:57,590 --> 00:08:59,570
So we can all get out of here.

131
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,010
It's the Chief.

132
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,620
Hello?

133
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:16,110
Are you okay? How's your head?

134
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:18,440
I'm okay.

135
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:23,180
The results will be out in a
few hours. Take care until then.

136
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:24,970
Relay this to Dr. Cha.

137
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:28,370
Keep the medical team under
control until we get the final results,

138
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:30,400
and call if any emergency arises.

139
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,460
Okay.

140
00:09:31,460 --> 00:09:32,930
Also...

141
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:36,710
there's a chance it's
not the Nipah virus.

142
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:39,890
Dr. Cha went in there?

143
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:41,550
During a crisis like this,

144
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:44,370
isn't keeping protocol
basic and the best way?

145
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:48,020
He has no principles at all.

146
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:51,300
He's always been like this.
He's totally uncontrollable!

147
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:56,480
If Dr. Cha hadn't gone in, the juvenile
diabetes patient would've been in danger.

148
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:59,840
Dr. Cha keeps saying it might
not be the Nipah virus.

149
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:03,070
But how can it be proven right now?

150
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:05,900
Yes, we have a suspected
patient at our hospital.

151
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:09,010
Until we have the results,
I won't tolerate rash decisions.

152
00:10:09,010 --> 00:10:12,750
Also, Dr. Cha entering the center,
regardless of the results...

153
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:15,110
He must face the consequences.

154
00:10:25,510 --> 00:10:27,360
I've thought this before, but

155
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,620
you can't draw, Dr. Cha.

156
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:58,160
Don't remove your
protective equipment.

157
00:10:59,430 --> 00:11:01,850
Not until we get out of here.

158
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,880
You gave up so soon.

159
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:11,210
It's not like you'll leave
because I tell you to.

160
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:13,740
You won't sit still here, either.

161
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:15,310
Telling you will be a
waste of my time.

162
00:11:15,310 --> 00:11:16,970
Then you shouldn't have fallen.

163
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:24,260
- Dr. Lee Yoo Joon.
- Yes?

164
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,800
Okay. Focus.

165
00:11:29,810 --> 00:11:31,070
As you can see,

166
00:11:31,070 --> 00:11:33,380
his entire body is
susceptible right now.

167
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:36,460
Dr. Cha, we got a call
from the KCDC earlier.

168
00:11:36,460 --> 00:11:39,290
The patient's friend who got
back from India last week.

169
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:40,330
How is he?

170
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:42,120
He had a slight fever
after coming back to Korea,

171
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:45,190
and it lasted a few days.
He's fine now.

172
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:48,500
It could be a minor infection,
or infection without symptoms.

173
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:52,290
We can't totally eliminate the
possibility of the Nipah virus.

174
00:11:52,290 --> 00:11:53,610
Of course, that's still open.

175
00:11:53,610 --> 00:11:57,300
However, he has symptoms
unexplainable by the Nipah virus.

176
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:00,260
But we can't run a CT
nor an MRI here.

177
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:02,090
- Can we diagnose him?
- We must try.

178
00:12:02,090 --> 00:12:04,470
Us, doctors, will be the
examination equipment.

179
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:06,970
We become the
examination equipment?

180
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:12,430
Can you all hear me?

181
00:12:12,430 --> 00:12:14,270
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, Dr. Cha.

182
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,580
A 68-year old male.

183
00:12:17,580 --> 00:12:20,400
Chronic headaches,
loss of appetite, and

184
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,640
fatigue for a year.

185
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:24,150
Vomiting and chest pains
started recently.

186
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:27,400
And now, faster pulse, disorientation,
seizure, and palpitations.

187
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,870
New symptoms have appeared.

188
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:32,400
Dr. Cha thinks this patient
may not have the Nipah virus.

189
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,600
Starting now, each person
takes one system.

190
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:37,780
We'll figure out what could
turn into systemic disease.

191
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:39,440
First-year Kim Won Hee, the lungs.

192
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,400
Yes, sir.

193
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,740
Second-year Kang Shi Young, the heart.

194
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:44,490
Yes, sir.

195
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:46,250
Third-year Kang Mi Rae,
the metabolic system.

196
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,650
Yes, sir.

197
00:12:47,650 --> 00:12:49,520
Third-year Heo Joon, the brain.

198
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:51,190
Yes, sir.

199
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:53,180
Dr. Lee Yoo Joon, the digestive system.

200
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,200
- Yes, sir.
- I'll oversee the entire diagnosis.

201
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:56,130
Let's start.

202
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:57,430
Yes, sir.

203
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:02,400
[ Chronic lung disease ]

204
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:08,000
Dr. Cha, could it be
a chronic lung disease?

205
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,200
It's associated with chest pains,

206
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,600
fatigue, and palpitations.

207
00:13:12,890 --> 00:13:13,800
What about the heart?

208
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,010
No high blood pressure,
obesity, nor diabetes.

209
00:13:16,010 --> 00:13:18,620
No conditions that
could affect his heart.

210
00:13:18,620 --> 00:13:21,930
No history of myocardial infarction, angina,
nor cardiac insufficiency either.

211
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:23,330
What about his X-rays?

212
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,400
[ Chronic Lung Disease
Chest X-ray ]

213
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:28,510
There's a slight
pneumonic infiltration.

214
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:30,150
Pneumonic infiltration?
[ Pneumonic infiltration:
When an infection spreads to the lungs ]

215
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:31,110
Next.

216
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:33,750
The arteriovenous malformation in
his brain and spinal cord

217
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,470
is affecting his entire body.

218
00:13:35,470 --> 00:13:38,840
In relation to his headaches,
seizures, and dysaesthesia.

219
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:41,130
Is the patient's name Yoo Deok Gyu?

220
00:13:41,130 --> 00:13:43,400
Yes. But why?

221
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,470
Does he have white hair
by any chance?

222
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,510
Is Dr. Kang in the security room also?

223
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:51,050
She didn't see him,
how would she know?

224
00:13:51,050 --> 00:13:52,340
Do you know him?

225
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,500
Yes.

226
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,800
I think so.

227
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:59,600
This is the best news so far.

228
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,740
Do you know him well?

229
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:04,050
I saw him during my volunteer work,
so I don't know him too well.

230
00:14:04,050 --> 00:14:05,790
But I do know his occupation.

231
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:06,880
What is it?

232
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:09,890
He's a Catholic priest.

233
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:15,860
He has a rosary ring.

234
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:17,270
A priest...

235
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,980
What is he like?

236
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:21,550
As a religious figure
or a regular person.

237
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:25,990
He is a good man
regardless of his religion.

238
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:29,530
He did more volunteer work
and good deeds than others.

239
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,600
This really puzzles me sometimes.

240
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,200
I don't have a religion,
but I get curious.

241
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,800
If there is a God,

242
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:39,330
why would he allow a good,
religious man to suffer?

243
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:42,850
Because that's religion.

244
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:45,180
Religion makes people suffer?

245
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,660
How is his build? Is he thin?

246
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,430
Yes, why?

247
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,500
[ Height 168cm, Weight 67kg ]

248
00:14:52,540 --> 00:14:54,570
Here's an additional symptom.

249
00:14:54,570 --> 00:14:56,710
Rapid weight loss.

250
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,850
He seems to have lost at least

251
00:14:58,850 --> 00:15:00,870
20kg from six months ago.

252
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:03,120
He was a bit stockier back then.

253
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,680
Any ailment which could
cause weight loss?

254
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:06,750
No.

255
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:09,660
He doesn't have diabetes
or any thyroid diseases.

256
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:12,250
But we don't know
about cancer or infection.

257
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:16,500
He didn't have any
geriatric diseases, either.

258
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,470
Why would all these
symptoms start a year ago?

259
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:34,380
Miss, are you okay?

260
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:36,920
What's wrong?

261
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:39,240
My arm hurts so much...

262
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:43,740
Dr. Cha, Lee Da Hae is
experiencing pain in her arm.

263
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:45,420
Please sedate her first.

264
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:47,850
Miss, are you okay?

265
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:50,620
Dr. Heo Joon.

266
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:52,670
Sunbae.

267
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:04,450
Heo Joon, snap out of it.

268
00:16:05,730 --> 00:16:06,970
Sunbae!

269
00:16:08,090 --> 00:16:11,430
Yes, yes, Dr. Cha. I'm here.

270
00:16:11,430 --> 00:16:12,680
Take care of it.

271
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:16,150
You promised to take care of it.

272
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,020
Longer the delay, the harder it'll be.

273
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,620
For both you and the patient.

274
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:28,350
- Dr. Cha...
- Say it.

275
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,330
I'll subdue her pain first.

276
00:16:32,330 --> 00:16:34,650
She's suffering so much.

277
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:36,330
Analgesic.

278
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:39,300
Miss, we'll administer an analgesic.

279
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,460
What's the reason?

280
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:04,780
The reason you decided
to come forward.

281
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:11,040
If she's experiencing phantom
limb pains, it may not be your fault.

282
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:12,860
I know that...

283
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:15,610
her pain may not be my fault.

284
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:19,000
But if I keep hiding it...

285
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:23,430
then it'll be harder to diagnose her.

286
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:27,290
Get ready.

287
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:29,880
I'm going in, too?

288
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,340
I like what you said.

289
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:35,060
It wasn't to lessen your guilt,

290
00:17:35,060 --> 00:17:37,360
or because you felt
sorry for the patient.

291
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,300
It was for an accurate diagnosis.

292
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:54,600
Sir.

293
00:17:56,190 --> 00:17:58,820
Sir, are you awake?

294
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:01,910
Mr. Yoo Deok Gyu.

295
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:05,430
I'm Dr. Cha Yo Han of
Dept. of Pain Medicine.

296
00:18:05,430 --> 00:18:06,920
Can you hear me?

297
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,010
Yes.

298
00:18:08,010 --> 00:18:10,110
I'll ask a few questions.

299
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:13,810
You had a sudden weight
loss recently, correct?

300
00:18:13,810 --> 00:18:15,090
Yes.

301
00:18:15,090 --> 00:18:17,360
Why did you lose so much weight?

302
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,390
Because I have no appetite.

303
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:21,350
A typical loss of appetite

304
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:23,260
won't cause such
a rapid weight loss.

305
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:24,880
There must be other reasons.

306
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:27,470
Truthfully...

307
00:18:28,460 --> 00:18:30,080
starting a few months ago,

308
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,870
I started taking sleeping pills.

309
00:18:31,870 --> 00:18:33,550
That's when I...

310
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:35,380
started vomiting,

311
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:37,620
and losing weight.

312
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:40,830
We don't see sleeping pill
prescription in your chart though.

313
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,020
Did you acquire them
somewhere else...

314
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:47,320
and not the hospital?

315
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:49,700
Sir.

316
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,400
[ Ended group call ]

317
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:03,340
What the? Why did we get cut off?

318
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:05,140
Try calling again.

319
00:19:08,150 --> 00:19:09,560
Sir.

320
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:13,200
Whatever you say in here,
it'll be kept confidential.

321
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:18,400
We're obligated not to
release patients' information.

322
00:19:18,460 --> 00:19:21,380
So please tell us.

323
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:25,100
Why you took sleeping pills and
why there's no prescription record.

324
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:38,920
I didn't get a prescription.

325
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:41,820
I collected them...

326
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:43,830
for many decades.

327
00:19:50,150 --> 00:19:52,160
We solved one element.

328
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:54,700
An overdose of sleeping pills

329
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:56,810
could lead to vomiting.

330
00:19:56,810 --> 00:19:59,400
But the weight loss can't be
solely due to vomiting.

331
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,510
My illness...

332
00:20:01,590 --> 00:20:04,150
probably won't get any better.

333
00:20:04,150 --> 00:20:07,920
You won't find the cause, either.

334
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,320
Why is that?

335
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,560
Didn't you come here to get well?

336
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,240
Of course, I want to get well.

337
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,800
But...

338
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:29,920
Sir.

339
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,850
You have a religion, correct?

340
00:20:33,850 --> 00:20:37,650
Why does God inflict
pain on mankind?

341
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:40,350
Since you're human,

342
00:20:40,350 --> 00:20:43,620
I'm sure you've asked
this to the Heavens.

343
00:20:43,620 --> 00:20:46,230
"I live such a faithful life.

344
00:20:46,230 --> 00:20:47,730
Why do you make me suffer?"

345
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,890
What is your answer to this?

346
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,490
My sins.

347
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:03,340
I'm paying for my sins.

348
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:05,790
- Your sins?
- Yes.

349
00:21:07,610 --> 00:21:08,650
I...

350
00:21:11,090 --> 00:21:13,620
killed people.

351
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:17,670
I've killed so many people.

352
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:20,470
No matter...

353
00:21:20,470 --> 00:21:23,080
how many good deeds
I do and repent...

354
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:25,790
I've committed unforgivable sins.

355
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,650
What?

356
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:41,100
What did you say?

357
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,500
Sir, are you okay?

358
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:55,340
Kang Shi Young, make a sound.

359
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,230
It's a nerve issue.

360
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:02,540
His saturation and BP are dropping.

361
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:04,420
Give him oxygen and
12g of ephedrine.

362
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,180
- Maximize the fluid flow.
- Okay!

363
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:16,290
What's going on?

364
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:17,650
I'm not sure.

365
00:22:22,530 --> 00:22:24,180
Miss, are you okay?

366
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:26,570
Please hang on.

367
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:29,110
Dr. Heo,

368
00:22:29,110 --> 00:22:31,710
Lee Da Hae is awake now.

369
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,890
Are you feeling okay?

370
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:48,070
I must seem crazy, right?

371
00:22:48,070 --> 00:22:49,110
Pardon?

372
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:57,310
I keep saying my arm hurts

373
00:22:57,310 --> 00:23:00,020
when I don't even have one.

374
00:23:00,020 --> 00:23:04,220
Everyone thinks I must be crazy.

375
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:06,310
My parents...

376
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:08,110
and my friends.

377
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:09,410
No, you're not.

378
00:23:09,410 --> 00:23:13,060
I promise you it's not
a psychological problem.

379
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,390
Then what is it?

380
00:23:14,390 --> 00:23:17,560
We would need to run some tests,

381
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:20,240
but the pain from
your amputated arm...

382
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,490
is probably a phantom limb pain.

383
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:23,870
Phantom limb pain?

384
00:23:23,870 --> 00:23:25,890
After an amputation,

385
00:23:25,890 --> 00:23:29,310
you feel pain in that area.

386
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:31,980
Why would such an illness exist?

387
00:23:40,370 --> 00:23:41,810
First,

388
00:23:41,810 --> 00:23:44,380
because something
might be wrong...

389
00:23:44,380 --> 00:23:46,140
with your neuro nerve signals.

390
00:23:47,180 --> 00:23:48,530
And second...

391
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,200
What?

392
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,630
What is it?

393
00:24:08,610 --> 00:24:09,750
What's going on?

394
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,900
- What's wrong with Dr. Heo?
- What's going on?

395
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:17,280
I'm sorry.

396
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,670
I'm so sorry.

397
00:24:29,110 --> 00:24:31,110
[ Reason for hospitalization ]

398
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:32,360
[ X-ray ]

399
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:36,000
During your amputation surgery...

400
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:50,100
there was an interruption in the
anesthesia due to my error.

401
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,900
[ BIS: Bispectral index,
40 - 60 for general anesthesia ]

402
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,770
Interruption in the anesthesia?

403
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:05,680
It's when you wake up

404
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,560
during anesthesia and feel stimuli.

405
00:25:08,530 --> 00:25:11,720
Since you were administered
a muscle relaxant,

406
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:15,770
you would've been immobilized...

407
00:25:15,770 --> 00:25:19,190
but felt the pain in its entirety.

408
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:23,100
So the second reason...

409
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:24,800
is that?

410
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,150
We don't know the exact cause

411
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,750
of your phantom limb pain.

412
00:25:33,170 --> 00:25:35,160
But my error was...

413
00:25:36,310 --> 00:25:38,140
a contributing factor.

414
00:25:40,130 --> 00:25:41,950
I'm so sorry.

415
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,210
Get away from me.

416
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:49,030
I said, get away from me!

417
00:25:49,030 --> 00:25:51,540
I don't want you near me!

418
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,600
- Miss, are you okay?
- Get lost!

419
00:25:55,910 --> 00:25:57,340
Please calm down.

420
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:58,670
Stay away!

421
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:05,810
Did that...

422
00:26:06,890 --> 00:26:09,350
Did that really happen, Sunbae?

423
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:25,560
♫ You were going through your life,
there was time to play ♫

424
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,790
♫ Yesterday ♫

425
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:37,210
♫ But the light in your eyes,
did it start to fade ♫

426
00:26:37,210 --> 00:26:39,340
♫ To fade away ♫

427
00:26:40,650 --> 00:26:41,930
Dr. Cha.

428
00:26:41,930 --> 00:26:44,040
His lower chin area is swollen.

429
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:49,300
Lymphadenia.
[ Lymphadenia: Swelling of the lymph nodes ]

430
00:26:49,300 --> 00:26:51,300
[ Lymphadenia: Swelling of the lymph nodes ]

431
00:26:53,010 --> 00:26:54,570
[ Lymphadenia ]

432
00:26:54,570 --> 00:26:57,190
It's either an infection or a tumor.

433
00:26:57,190 --> 00:26:59,830
If it's a tumor, there's
no way for us to check it here.

434
00:26:59,830 --> 00:27:02,190
Lymphadenia, disorientation
with no sense of directions,

435
00:27:02,190 --> 00:27:03,500
and loss of hearing.

436
00:27:04,570 --> 00:27:06,620
It could be an infection.

437
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,100
What could it be?

438
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:14,790
His medical records were
clean up until a year ago.

439
00:27:14,790 --> 00:27:17,060
Without any signs or symptoms.

440
00:27:17,060 --> 00:27:19,690
Why is he bombarded
with symptoms suddenly?

441
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,670
The incubation period.

442
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:27,740
What if a long incubation illness
started showing signs a year ago?

443
00:27:27,740 --> 00:27:30,860
Those diseases are
usually from overseas.

444
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:33,340
- He hasn't been overseas, correct?
- No.

445
00:27:33,340 --> 00:27:35,610
He hasn't been on
a plane in 40 years.

446
00:27:35,610 --> 00:27:37,080
40 years?

447
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:40,180
Then he was overseas
40 years ago?

448
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:41,840
I'm not sure...

449
00:27:45,910 --> 00:27:47,950
I think he could have.

450
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:52,920
War...

451
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,430
War.

452
00:27:55,430 --> 00:27:56,730
What?

453
00:27:56,730 --> 00:27:58,550
He said, "war."

454
00:27:58,550 --> 00:28:00,470
Right before he had
trouble breathing.

455
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:03,700
Then when he said he
killed many people...

456
00:28:03,700 --> 00:28:05,700
Did he fight in a war?

457
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:09,300
He collected sleeping pills suffering
from his insomnia for a long time...

458
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,890
because of his war memories.

459
00:28:10,890 --> 00:28:13,840
What if that war took
place overseas?

460
00:28:18,430 --> 00:28:20,750
Patient Yoo Deok Gyu.

461
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:22,800
68 years old.
[ Yoo Deok Gyu ]

462
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:24,430
Born in 1950.

463
00:28:24,430 --> 00:28:28,220
Therefore, a war that
took place after 1970.

464
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:37,700
We are to identify all overseas
wars our patient could've been in.

465
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:39,510
our patient could've been in.

466
00:28:39,510 --> 00:28:40,850
If we're correct,

467
00:28:40,850 --> 00:28:43,570
he contracted a bacteria from
overseas causing his illness.

468
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:46,120
The timeline should be after 1970.

469
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:49,470
A war which Korean males
born in 1950 participated in...

470
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:52,340
The Vietnam War.

471
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:53,390
That's right.

472
00:28:53,390 --> 00:28:55,120
When I volunteered with him,

473
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:57,500
we met some Vietnam vets.

474
00:28:57,500 --> 00:28:59,430
- Thank you.
- You're well, right?

