00:29:28,650 --> 00:29:30,200
Melioidosis.
[ Melioidosis: Infectious disease
from contaminated soil or water ]

478
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,900
[ Melioidosis: Infectious disease
from contaminated soil or water ]

479
00:29:31,910 --> 00:29:33,680
It has a long incubation period.

480
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,950
If it's from Vietnam, then it's melioidosis.

481
00:29:35,950 --> 00:29:38,120
By melioidosis, you mean...

482
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:40,600
- Whitmore's disease?
- Yes, Whitmore's disease.

483
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,870
The bacteria was
dormant for 44 years?

484
00:29:42,870 --> 00:29:45,120
There's a case which
surfaced after 63 years.

485
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:48,600
That patient contracted it
during World War II.

486
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,510
Dr. Cha is right.

487
00:29:50,510 --> 00:29:52,150
The incubation period is long,

488
00:29:52,150 --> 00:29:54,940
but symptoms appear all over,
making it hard to diagnose.

489
00:29:54,940 --> 00:29:58,020
Until the symptoms turn septic,
it's hard to find the cause.

490
00:29:58,020 --> 00:30:00,190
It's rarely contagious,

491
00:30:00,190 --> 00:30:02,470
but the mortality rate is high at 40%.

492
00:30:13,530 --> 00:30:14,770
What is it, Dr. Cha?

493
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,240
We need a definite diagnosis.

494
00:30:18,240 --> 00:30:21,560
If he has an infection,
then it's definitely melioidosis.

